(honest re-measurement after the v9 audit; see v10.md)

2D torus L=16. For each disorder: K, richness(spectral-PR), eta^2 (field variance explained by the winding class):

  disorder=0.10: K= 48  richness=  2.3  eta^2(class-carried)=1.000  (class carries field)
  disorder=0.25: K= 25  richness=  2.6  eta^2(class-carried)=1.000  (class carries field)
  disorder=0.50: K= 10  richness=  3.4  eta^2(class-carried)=1.000  (class carries field)
  disorder=0.90: K=  1  richness= 15.8  eta^2(class-carried)=0.000  (richness is DISORDER, not class)
  disorder=1.60: K=  1  richness= 50.9  eta^2(class-carried)=0.000  (richness is DISORDER, not class)

  => No regime has BOTH high richness AND high eta^2. Low disorder: large K,
     high eta^2, but low richness (plane waves). High disorder: high richness,
     but eta^2 -> 0 (disorder noise, not class). The 'harmonic completion' adds no
     genuine per-target structure: the Holonomy Code is NOT a generativity mechanism.
     (Contrast: the NCA codebook v6-v8 PASSES held-out realizability = high eta^2.)

